QUESTION:
3. Write a Java program to perform the following operations on a set of students
using arrays:

• Input and Display:
Accept N students’ roll numbers and names. Store them in parallel
arrays. Display the roll numbers and names as entered.

• Remove Duplicates:
Remove any duplicate roll numbers and their corresponding names.
Display the unique list of students.

• Search for a Student:
Prompt the user to enter a roll number to search. If found in the unique
list, print the student’s name and index; otherwise, print -1.

• Display in Reverse Order:
Display the unique students’ roll numbers and names in reverse order.


JAVA CODE:

package Array;
import java.util.Scanner;
public class SetOfStudents {
	public static void main(String[] args) {
		
		Scanner in=new Scanner(System.in);
		System.out.print("Enter the no.of Students: ");
		int n=in.nextInt();
		 
		System.out.println();
		int[] roll_no=new int[n];
		String[] name=new String[n];
		System.out.println("        Enter the student details");
		System.out.println("First ==> Roll number");
		System.out.println("Next ==> Name");
		          //Getting input
		
		
		for(int i=0;i<n;i++) 
		{	
			roll_no[i]=in.nextInt();
			in.nextLine();
            name[i] = in.nextLine();
		}
		           
		
		         //Display the input
		
		for(int j=0;j<n;j++)
		{
			System.out.println((j+1)+". Roll_no of Student : "+roll_no[j]);
			System.out.println("   Name of the Student : "+ name[j]);
			System.out.println();
		}
		           //Remove duplicate
		       
		int[] unique_roll=new int[n];
		String[] unique_name=new String[n];
		int ns=0;
		for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
		{
			boolean dup=false;
			for(int j=0;j<ns;j++)
			{
				if(roll_no[i]==unique_roll[j] || name[i]==unique_name[j]) {
					dup=true;
					break;
				}
			}
			
			if(!dup)
			{
				unique_roll[ns]=roll_no[i];
				unique_name[ns]=name[i];
				ns++;
			}
		}
		         //Print Unique list of student
		
		System.out.println();
		System.out.print("**Unique roll number : ");
		for(int i=0;i<ns;i++)
		{
			System.out.print(unique_roll[i]+"  ");
		}
		System.out.println();
		System.out.print("**Unique name : ");
		for(int i=0;i<ns;i++)
		{
			System.out.print(unique_name[i]+"  ");
		}
		        //Search for the student
		
		System.out.println();
		System.out.println("Enter the Roll number to find the Student : ");
		int Search_roll=in.nextInt();
		int flag =0;
		for(int i=0;i<ns;i++)
		{
			if(Search_roll==unique_roll[i])
			{
				flag=1;
				System.out.println("Name of the student is ["+unique_name[i]+"] index is ["+i+"]");
			}
			
		}
		if(flag==0)
		{
			System.out.println("-1");
			System.out.println("Roll no "+Search_roll+" is not in the unique list");
		}
		
		        //Display the reverse
		
		System.out.println();
		System.out.println();
		System.out.println("        Reverse order of the given list ");
		for(int k=ns-1;k>=0;k--)
		{
			System.out.println((k+1)+". Roll_no of Student : "+unique_roll[k]);
			System.out.println("   Name of Student : "+ name[k]);
		}
		
	}

}

OUTPUT:

